    <abstract> Located in Shexian county, Hebei, Foyannao cliff statues were constructed primarily during the third year 
        of the Jiayou era during the Northern Song Dynasty. A total of 37 statues in eight niches were preserved, and each statue was 
        identified with clear inscription records including the statue’s theme, construction time, donors, vow content, and processes 
        of repairing and construction. This survey report provides important material evidence for the study of Buddhist statues and 
        Buddhism in the Northern Song Dynasty.
    </abstract>
